==English==
===Etymology===
Brand name used by exporters for one of several varieties of Chinese goosberry selectively bred in New Zealand; named after the native bird known as the [[kiwi]].
===Alternative spellings===
*[[kiwifruit]]
===Noun===
'''[[kiwi]] [[fruit]]''' (''plural'' '''kiwi fruit''')

#A [[Chinese goosberry]] vine fruit, having a hairy brown skin and dark green (or in the case of the [[kiwi fruit gold]], yellow) flesh with fine black seeds.

====Synonyms====
*[[Chinese gooseberry]], [[kiwi]] (''colloquial''; ''US, rarely in [[New Zealand]]'')

